\input{regression-test}
% B5 — `warn_if_shadows` warns but still inserts the dead alias.
%
% scholatex.lua:43-55 detects a let name that shadows a built-in tag,
% block, or style word; it prints a warning to stderr and STILL inserts
% the entry into ALIAS / MACRO / BLOCKALIAS. Since dispatch always
% prefers built-ins, the user's entry is dead -- but the warning text
% says "ignored" which is technically correct only because nobody reads
% the entry.
%
% This MWE redefines `box` as an alias. The let is "ignored" but the
% ALIAS["box"] dict entry still exists. A clean implementation would
% return early after the warning so the alias table is honest.
%
% The body uses the built-in <box> block normally.
\documentclass[lang=en]{scholatex}
\begin{document}

let box = <line Navy>

<box line:Navy fill:AliceBlue>{
hello world
}

\end{document}
